import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['values'], bins=20, color='green', alpha=0.8)
    plt.axvline(data['values'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['values'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['values'].median(), color='blue', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['values'].median():.2f}")
    plt.legend(loc='upper right')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of values in the volcano dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.boxplot(data['values'])
    ax.axhline(y=data['values'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='-', label=f"Mean: {data['values'].mean():.2f}")
    ax.legend()
    plt.title("What is the average value in the volcano dataset?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.scatter(data['width'], data['height'])
    plt.title('Is there a correlation between width and height in the volcano dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    highest_value = data['values'].max()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.bar(data.index, data['values'])
    ax.axhline(highest_value, color='red', label=f'Highest Value: {highest_value:.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the highest value in the volcano dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    unique_values = data['values'].nunique()
    unique_values_count = data['values'].value_counts().sort_index()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.bar(unique_values_count.index, unique_values_count.values)
    ax.set_xlabel('Unique Values')
    ax.set_ylabel('Count')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of unique values in the volcano dataset?')
    ax.axvline(x=unique_values, color='red', label=f'Unique Values: {unique_values:.2f}')
    ax.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
